HEADWORD: Imburse
<hw>Im*burse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>burse</ets>: cf. F. <ets>embourser</ets> to put
into one's purse. See <er>Burse</er>, and <er>Purse</er>.]</ety> <def>To
supply or stock with money.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

